{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Legislate to limit interest rates on lending during Covid-19 outbreak",
        "additional_details": "As people lose their jobs and income, the first port of call for survival for many will be credit cards and overdrafts.\r\n \r\nThe Central Banks have reduced interest rates to near zero, yet many credit card companies and banks still charge 20+%, and many banks are increasing the interest rate for overdrafts to 39.9%.\r\n \r\nLegislate an emergency measure to cap interest on lending, including credit cards and loans, to a maximum, such as 3%, so people can weather this storm.",
        "background": "Legislate to put a temporary maximum interest rate, such as 3%, on all lending, such as credit card and overdraft debt.",
